Shocking video footage shows the woman raising the air rifle while striding down a road in Swinton, Salford. Greater Manchester Police has confirmed that a 34-year-old woman has been arrested on suspicion of possession of a firearm. Officers carrying out a search at a property have seized the weapon along with four knives. A spokeswoman for Greater Manchester Police said the woman has been released under investigation pending further enquiries. Witnesses described the woman as having a focused look on her face as she paced the street. An onlooker, who was with his children at the time, said his daughter noticed the woman and burst into tears.  Recalling the ordeal, he told The Sun: "I went into shock." Greater Manchester Police confirmed in a statement: "A 34-year-old woman was arrested on suspicion of possession of a firearm and possession of an offensive weapon. "Officers later searched an address and seized a weapon, confirmed as an air rifle, along with four knives." 